external_knowledge:
- 'Well-maintained sensors' refers to sensors that have been maintained within the last year; 
- 'Spring cleaning' is a metaphor for maintenance; 
- 'Climate conditions' refer to temperature and humidity readings.

Sensor 1 refers to a specific sensor with the identifier '1'; 
The month of May 2023 refers to the time period between '2023-05-01 00:00:00' and '2023-05-31 23:59:59';
Maintenance date refers to the date when maintenance was performed on the sensor.

sql:
SELECT MIN(min_temp) AS min_temperature
FROM data_summary
WHERE sensor_id = 1;
